{
  "stem": "5188.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we was talking about my sister's school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Normally, after having spent the first four grades at a folkshul, which is like an elementary school, there was a separation of the people who stayed in the elementary school to the eighth grade and then went to become an apprentice in some trade, or those who went on to higher learning.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The plan had been for my sister to go to a gymnasium, which normally, in Germany, start at the fifth grade.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They did in those days, anyway.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, the-- the gymnasium in Cologne was no longer for Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Jews were not allowed to go to the regular gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "However, there was a Jewish school in Cologne called the Yavneh.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my sister went to the Yavneh.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, the Yavneh was a relatively religious school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was quite Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that was a bit difficult for my sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But there were so many non-Orthodox Jewish children going to the Yavneh, because they couldn't go anywhere else anymore; so that she soon fit in very nicely, and had a circle of friends, and did very well.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So this was a school which really prepared Jewish children for higher learning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- but it was a Jewish school, and it was only for the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this was a real change.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Normally, my parents wouldn't have sent her to a school like the Yavneh.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there was no other way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] How did things change?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How did you know that your sister could no longer go to the school she originally would have gone to?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know exactly how it happened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But obviously, my-- when my parents-- I think, when they applied to the other school, they were told that they don't take Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
